<div class="content-section">
<h2>What Superpower Health actually is</h2>
<p>Superpower, founded in 2023, is an annual subscription service that combines comprehensive biomarker testing with an AI-powered health dashboard and concierge messaging access to a clinical team. The pitch is simple: the markers that preventive cardiologists and longevity physicians use to assess long-term risk &#8212; <a href="/biomarkers/apob">ApoB</a>, full hormone panels, advanced metabolic markers, inflammatory markers &#8212; made available directly to consumers at a fraction of the cost of concierge medicine.</p>
<p>When you join, you book a blood draw at one of 3,000+ Quest Diagnostics locations (or pay extra for a mobile phlebotomist). Results arrive in the Superpower dashboard within 3&#8211;7 days, translated into 17 health score categories with plain-language explanations, a personalized protocol, and a biological age calculation. Ongoing access to a concierge team via messaging is included in the base membership.</p>

<div class="callout">
<div class="callout-label">Affiliate disclosure</div>
<p>AgelessLabs has an affiliate relationship with Superpower. If you sign up via our link, we may earn a commission &#8212; at no additional cost to you. This review reflects our independent assessment. <a href="https://superpower.com/welcome?dub_id=d99GM8QoZlGRZs2y" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Sign up for Superpower &#8594;</a></p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
<h2>What&#8217;s included &#8212; and what the &#8220;100+ biomarkers&#8221; claim really means</h2>
<p>The &#8220;100+ biomarkers&#8221; headline is accurate in aggregate but worth understanding precisely. The base panel includes roughly 80 directly measured markers from a single blood draw. The remaining count includes algorithmically derived ratios &#8212; calculations like TG/HDL, non-HDL cholesterol, and other composite indices derived from primary measurements. This distinction matters because Function Health filed a false advertising lawsuit in January 2026 specifically challenging Superpower&#8217;s biomarker count claims, arguing that derived ratios should not be counted equivalently to direct measurements.</p>
<p>That said, the directly measured markers cover the longevity fundamentals comprehensively:</p>

