<p>Notable omissions from the base panel: <a href="/biomarkers/lipoprotein-a">Lp(a)</a> and the <a href="/biomarkers/omega-3-index">omega-3 index</a> are available as paid add-ons, not included by default. Heavy metals and cancer screening markers are not part of Superpower&#8217;s current offering at any tier &#8212; this is where Function Health has a meaningful edge.</p>

<div class="warning-callout">
<div class="warning-callout-label">The Function vs. Superpower lawsuit</div>
<p>In January 2026, Function Health filed a false advertising lawsuit against Superpower, alleging the &#8220;100+ biomarkers&#8221; claim misleads consumers by including algorithmically derived ratios alongside directly measured markers. The case (Function Health v. Superpower Health, C.D. Cal. 2026) is pending as of this writing. Both companies remain fully operational. We mention it not to adjudicate the dispute, but because it&#8217;s material information for anyone comparing the two services.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="content-section">
<h2>The platform experience</h2>
<p>Superpower&#8217;s dashboard is one of its genuine differentiators. Results are presented in clean, category-organized cards with plain-language explanations for each marker &#8212; what it measures, why it matters, what your value means, and what lifestyle, nutritional, or supplement changes may help. The AI chat feature has been live longer than Function Health&#8217;s comparable tool and is consistently described as more conversational and personalized in head-to-head comparisons.</p>
<p>The biological age score and 17-category health scoring system give you a concrete baseline to track over time. The &#8220;Bring Your Own Data&#8221; feature lets you upload historical PDF lab results &#8212; Superpower digitizes them and builds trend lines before you even complete your first Superpower draw. For anyone with years of prior bloodwork, this is a meaningful feature that Function Health doesn&#8217;t offer.</p>
<p>Concierge messaging &#8212; unlimited SMS access to a clinical team &#8212; is included. This is not a one-on-one physician relationship, but for clarifying what a specific result means or whether a value warrants follow-up, it fills a real gap.</p>
</div>

