<div class="content-section">
<h2>Who Superpower is right for</h2>
<p>Superpower is the right choice if you want a comprehensive first baseline without spending more than $200, you&#8217;re new to advanced biomarker testing, or you want AI-powered results interpretation built into the experience. It&#8217;s an especially good fit for anyone who has accumulated years of prior lab results they want to consolidate and trend &#8212; the historical import feature makes Superpower immediately useful even before your first draw.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s less suited for someone who needs to test more than once per year (tracking a specific intervention, managing an active health issue), wants heavy metal or cancer marker coverage, or is specifically focused on the markers Superpower currently places behind add-on pricing &#8212; namely Lp(a) and omega-3 index.</p>
<p>For most of AgelessLabs&#8217; audience &#8212; health-conscious adults 35&#8211;65 who want to understand their longevity risk profile and haven&#8217;t yet done comprehensive testing &#8212; Superpower is the right starting point.</p>
</div>

