<div class="content-section">
<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-list">
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Superpower Health worth it?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">For most health-conscious adults, yes. At $199/year, Superpower delivers the longevity fundamentals &#8212; <a href="/biomarkers/apob">ApoB</a>, full hormone panel, inflammatory markers, thyroid, nutritional markers &#8212; at the lowest price point in the market. The honest caveats: one annual draw, some of the advertised biomarker count includes derived ratios, and Lp(a) requires an add-on. If you need twice-yearly testing or want cancer/heavy metal markers, <a href="/reviews/function-health">Function Health</a> is the better fit.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How does Superpower compare to Function Health?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">Superpower is $166/year cheaper with one annual draw and 100+ markers (including derived ratios). Function is $365/year with two draws and 160+ directly measured markers &#8212; including cancer markers, heavy metals, and ANA autoimmune screen. Superpower&#8217;s AI chat is more polished; Function&#8217;s twice-yearly cadence is a meaningful advantage for tracking interventions. See our full <a href="/reviews/function-health">Function Health review</a> for the detailed comparison.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What biomarkers does Superpower include?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">The base panel includes cardiovascular markers (<a href="/biomarkers/apob">ApoB</a>, LDL particle analysis, <a href="/biomarkers/hscrp">hsCRP</a>), full metabolic panel, sex hormones (testosterone, estradiol, DHEA-S, SHBG, progesterone), thyroid (TSH + free T3/T4), inflammatory markers, nutritional status (Vitamin D, B12, ferritin), and complete CBC and CMP. <a href="/biomarkers/lipoprotein-a">Lp(a)</a> and omega-3 index are available as add-ons.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Superpower available in all states?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">Available in most US states. New York and New Jersey members pay $399/year (double the standard rate) due to state regulatory requirements. Rhode Island has restrictions. Check superpower.com for current availability in your state.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I use HSA or FSA funds?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">Yes. Superpower is HSA/FSA eligible. Using pre-tax funds effectively reduces the real cost by 25&#8211;35% depending on your tax bracket &#8212; bringing the out-of-pocket cost of a $199 membership to approximately $130&#8211;$150.</div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Does Superpower require a lab visit?</div>
<div class="faq-answer">Yes &#8212; Superpower requires a venous blood draw. The lab draw at Quest Diagnostics is included in the base membership. A mobile phlebotomist home draw option is available for approximately $120 extra in most markets.</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<script>
function toggleFaq(el) {
const answer = el.nextElementSibling;
const isOpen = answer.classList.contains('open');
document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer.open').forEach(a => {
a.classList.remove('open');
a.previousElementSibling.classList.remove('open');
});
if (!isOpen) {
answer.classList.add('open');
el.classList.add('open');
}
}
</script>
